Third-party attribution
================================================================================

This project is a downstream port of the "oh-my-*" agent harness lineage
originated by code-yeongyu and Yeachan-Heo, both MIT-licensed. The skill
catalog, subagent role definitions, and workflow conventions in this
repository were derived from:

  oh-my-claudecode (OMC) by Yeachan-Heo
    Source : https://github.com/Yeachan-Heo/oh-my-claudecode
    License: MIT
    Used   : agents/*.md (executor, critic, architect, planner, debugger,
             code-reviewer, security-reviewer, test-engineer, analyst,
             git-master, document-specialist, designer) and skills/*
             (deep-interview, autopilot, code-review, plan, debug, ...)
             were referenced when authoring the Kimi-CLI-format equivalents
             under agents/ and skills/.

  oh-my-codex (OMX) by Yeachan-Heo
    Source : https://github.com/Yeachan-Heo/oh-my-codex
    License: MIT (license file pending upstream confirmation)
    Used   : the ralph / autopilot / deep-interview workflow design and
             the SKILL.md frontmatter convention used in skills/.

  oh-my-openagent (formerly oh-my-opencode) by code-yeongyu
    Source : https://github.com/code-yeongyu/oh-my-openagent
    License: MIT
    Used   : the broader "oh-my-* on a CLI host" design pattern that all
             downstream ports inherit.

Per the MIT terms of the upstream projects, the copyright notices above are
preserved verbatim. Modifications include but are not limited to:

  - YAML wrapper files (agents/*.yaml) targeting the Kimi CLI agent-spec
    schema documented at src/kimi_cli/agentspec.py.
  - Path rewrites .omc/ → .kimi/ and .omx/ → .kimi/ throughout skills.
  - Host-name rewrites Claude Code / Codex CLI → Kimi CLI in user-facing
    text.
  - Install scripts (scripts/install.sh, scripts/uninstall.sh) and hook
    templates targeting Kimi CLI's config.toml schema.

